question: Question: This poem's fifth stanza begins by stating that "it is strange to inhabit the earth no longer" and its fourth stanza begins by stating "Voices. Voices." For 10 points each: [10] Name this poem whose second stanza parenthetically remarks about struggles of "huge strange thoughts inside you / going and coming and often staying all night."
